Title: A Relation between the Anomalous Dimensions and OPE Coefficients in
  Asymptotic Free Field Theories
Authors: Hidenori Sonoda and Wang-Chang Su
Comments: 6 pages, plain TeX, uses harvmac
Report-no: UCLA/96/TEP/26
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B392 (1997) 141-144
\\
  In asymptotic free field theories we show that part of the OPE of the trace
of the stress-energy tensor and an arbitrary composite field is determined by
the anomalous dimension of the composite field. We take examples from the
two-dimensional O(N) non-linear sigma model.
